[4] Cholera - Angola
Date: Fri, 27 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: XinHuaNet [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200610/27/eng20061027_315755.html>

The WHO has announced that a total of 56 632 cases of cholera,
including 2314 deaths, have been reported in 16 out of the 18
provinces in Angola, since the beginning of the outbreak on 13 Feb 2006.
According to a press notice published by the WHO on Thu, 26 Oct 2006,
since the release of its last report on 27 Sep 2006, a total of 1942
new cases and 89 deaths have occurred countrywide and Lunda Sul and
Moxico are the [only] 2 provinces without cholera cases.
This year's outbreak of the water-borne disease in Angola has been
acknowledged by international relief organizations to be the
country's worst since independence over 3 decades ago.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
